SymfonyApp
==========

This foundamental framework/application with simple user/role management and CMS.
It is based on Symfony2 and it is for projects with most customer functionality which needs to be done by customer specification.

!!!THIS PROJECT IS AT THE BEGINNING OF THE DEVELOPMENT!!!

1) Installing
-------------

When it comes to installing the SymfonyApp, you have the
following options.

### Use Composer (*recommended*)

    curl -s http://getcomposer.org/installer | php

    php composer.phar install

Then, setup what the installator will ask you.

2) Checking your System Configuration
-------------------------------------

Before starting coding, make sure that your local system is properly
configured for Symfony.

Execute the `check.php` script from the command line:

    php app/check.php

3) Running the server

The easiest is to run PHP built server using:

    php app/console server:run


4) Browsing the Demo Application
--------------------------------

    http://localhost:8000/app_dev.php/


All libraries and bundles included in the Symfony Standard Edition are
released under the MIT or BSD license.

Enjoy!


